    <bodyTop>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>The Nursing Programme goals are to prepare highly educated and competent nurses ready to enter the workforce, providing high quality evidence informed person-centred nursing care. We aim to contribute to and disseminate the scholarly evidence-base in nursing and health care, foster excellence in teaching, provide service to the profession and other communities of interest and cooperate with health care, governmental, and related institutions to transfer knowledge in health sciences and health care.</p>
<p>Responding to the need to further develop and inform advancing practice, an approach has been taken across the nursing programme as part of a Person-centred Practice Framework, positioned in the School of Health Sciences at Queen Margaret University. </p>]]></Value>
    </bodyTop>
